<br>
<br>
&quot;Wake up you drunken idiot!&quot; Snarled the city guard as he clenched the hilt of his bastard sword.&quot;Get off your back and go about your business&quot;<br>
<br>
The naked human slightly opened his eyes and frowned. &quot;Ugh..&quot; he exclaimed as he put his arms over his eyes. &quot;What..where?&quot; <br>
<br>
The guard released the hilt of his weapon and snickered out of amusement. &quot;Too much of the dwarven ale eh?&quot; Said the guard with a dwarven accent. The guard kneeled down and shoved the human to his side. &quot;Go on, go home and wash your self. You look horrible.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I have never seen you around here, you must be from queynos?&quot; The guard inquired.<br>
<br>
The human nodded in agreement with a puzzled look on his face. &quot;I.. aye.. &quot;.He sat down and stared at the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;You look like shit, maybe a good bath and some clothing would do you good.&quot; Said the guard in a comical tone. &quot;You know we do have laws against civilians walking around naked and smelling like trolls&quot;.<br>
<br>
The human put out his arms and looked at them. Turning his hands, and bending his elbows, he tilted his head with a look of amusment upon his face.<br>
<br>
The guard chuckled at the naked human. &quot;You know what?&quot; asked the guard as he stood up. &quot;There is a tailor not too far from here, take these copper pieces and do me a favor&quot; Said the guard as he reached into his pocket for some change. &quot;Go and buy yourself a pair of pants&quot;<br>
<br>
The guard extended his arm out to the naked human with some change in his hand. &quot;Here take this...&quot;<br>
<br>
The human rubbed his eyes and looked at the guard. &quot;Thank you I guess&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well you ungrateful bastard!&quot; Scowled the guard as he threw the coins at the human. &quot;You best not be here by the time I return!&quot; <br>
<br>
The guard turned around and walked off. &quot;Or else its the city jail for you!&quot;<br>
<br>
The human looked at the ground and picked up the coins. &quot;Where am I?&quot; he asked himself. The human sighed and got on his feet. He looked around but couldn't see much of anything, It seemed as though there was a heavy morning fog. Faint noises of clattering metal could be heard from not too far. <br>
<br>
&quot;What am I here for?&quot; he asked himself as he walked around aimlessly. &quot;Clothing..  guess I must find something to wear before I get into any trouble&quot;. <br>
<br>
As he gained his posture, he walked towards the city noise. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
