<br>
Across the street he could see a little tent shop with leather clothing hanging from the ceiling and its sides. There also seemed to be a little being in the tent rocking about in her rocking chair. &quot;This must be it&quot;, he thought. There was a fair amount of people walking around browsing wears from other merchants. &quot;I can't draw attention to myself.. people will think I am a mad man on the loose!&quot;<br>
<br>
He was crouched behind a barrel of ale with a potent smell, glancing over it once every so often to find a good moment to cross the street.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Come all! Come see my fabulous wears from ancient dragons!&quot; Screamed a vendor. <br>
<br>
&quot;Perfect, this might just be my break.&quot; The human thought to himself. <br>
<br>
&quot;I have items for everyone! Come, Come all and purchase my wear! Temeilion has everything you wish!&quot; He shouted <br>
<br>
A massive stampede made its way to the back end of the road, leaving all other merchants wondering what it was that he had in stock.<br>
<br>
The human peeked up once more, looking both left and right he couldn't see anyone within range, nor anyone looking his way. With swiftness the human leaped from one side of the street to the other.<br>
<br>
&quot;Psst.&quot; Whispered the human.<br>
<br>
&quot;Eh? who goes about?&quot; Asked a little gnomish voice. &quot;Show yer self!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I am right here m'am, hiding beside your little tent.&quot; The human whispered again.<br>
<br>
&quot;I witnessed many kinds of tactics of stealing from merchants.. do you really think i will fall for this? HA! get lost before I call for guards!&quot; She scowled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Humm, no m'am, i am in a little bit of a bind here. You see I am somewhat without clothing and wanted to purchase a pair of pants from you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh yeah.. i beleive ye alright. Who would be dumb enough to walk around naked here.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Look m'am.. I only wish to buy a pair of those leather pants you have hanging there, t'is all i want.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;No, i have one better for you, SIR!, come out of there before I really get mad.&quot; The old woman seemed to be getting really irritated at this point and the human knew that his options were growing slim. <br>
<br>
&quot;Alight, fine... &quot; whispered the human. He looked both sides of the street and people were still rounded up with the famous dragon gear merchant. <br>
<br>
&quot;Come out now, I have no time nor patience for games!&quot; Snarled the old gnome while holding on to her broom&quot;<br>
<br>
The human quickly ran around the corner of the tent and into its opening, hastily looking for a spot to hide the human couldn't seem to find one.Then as he glanced in the back end of the tent he could see a pile of leather scraps, &quot;That might just do!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Eeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeep!&quot; Exclaimed the little gnome as she threw her arms up in the air. &quot;Oh my good heavens put some clothes on!&quot; Cried out the gnome while clutching her chest. <br>
<br>
The human landed in the pile of leather scraps and buried himself in it.<br>
<br>
&quot;That is what I have been trying to tell you m'am!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You never said you were naked! Good lord, I need a drink.&quot; said the gnome as she walked to a small keg in the back of the tent. <br>
<br>
&quot;M'am, please.. i beg of you, some pants&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh yes.. yes yes yes.. hmmmm&quot; thought the gnome. &quot;What size ye be?&quot; she asked. &quot;Oh wait nevermind.. i know exactly what size ye be.&quot; she snickered. She grabbed a pair of tan leather pants hanging from the mens section. &quot;Here these should fit you like a glove and bring out those nice... ummmm.&quot; she blushed and threw him the leather pants. &quot;Put these on while I pour myself some ale&quot;<br>
<br>
The human rolled his eyes and proceeded to slip into his pants.Putting his feet in wasn't the problem, but little leather scraps were also following into the pants. With a little struggle the human got his pants up and tied. brushing off and pulling out the rest of the scraps the human smiled. &quot;Thank you m'lady&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, young one&quot; Smiled the little gnome form behind the curtains.<br>
<br>
&quot;Here, I have these coppers, to cover the cost&quot;. Said the human.<br>
<br>
The little gnome walked out from behind the curtains and made her way to his hand, she counted the copper pieces and smiled. &quot;You are 4 copper pieces short, but It'll be fine.&quot; the gnome took the money from his hand and stuffed them into her pouch.&quot;Thank you.&quot;<br>
<br>
She sat in her chair and was looking at the human with an inquisitive regard, peering him up and down. <br>
<br>
The human looked at himself wondering what it was that she was looking at, &quot;What is wrong?&quot; he asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell me young lad, what be your name?&quot; she asked while rocking her little chair back and forth.<br>
<br>
The human suddenly took a step back with a puzzled look upon his face. &quot;Who am I?&quot; he asked himself. &quot;I cannot say my real name, for I do not exist anymore, and surely dragon slayers would come running after me&quot;, the human shut his eyes. trying to vividly remember something worthy of a name. His mental vision grew cloudy.<br>
<br>
Two golden eyes appeared in his vision, glowing with seering fire. &quot;Fallen dragon soul&quot; said the figure. &quot;You are a fallen dragon soul!&quot; Screamed the figure as a set of razor sharp teeth came at this face.<br>
<br>
The human was knocked to the floor as if he had been hit with a war hammer.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, what in the lords name does ye have, me name is Ebbie&quot; Smiled the little gnome.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am fallen dragon soul&quot; whispered the human.<br>
<br>
&quot;Phallen dragonsoul eh? your mother hate you?&quot; <br>
<br>
The human looked up at the gnome with a grin, &quot;Aye, Phallen Dragonsoul is my name.&quot; <br>
<br>
