<br>
Phallen pulled himself back on his two feet and brushed off his backside and smiled at her nodding in agreement.<br>
<br>
&quot;So, where is a nice young stud like yourself heading to?&quot; Ebbie inquired.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, I am not sure yet. I haven't really made any plans at the moment.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ebbie took a long sip from her ale and set down the mug on the little wooden table next to her. &quot;Where are you from?&quot; she asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Queynos...&quot; he replied.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahhhh yes.. I know Queynos all too well, What brings you to Freeport then?&quot;<br>
<br>
Phallen's eyes started to scan the room, quickly thinking for an answer.&quot;I came here for guidance&quot; he replied. Phallen knew that it wasn't guidance that he needed, what he really needed was a recollection of memories that he had prior to waking up in Freeport.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye... Me thinks I can help ye with that Phallen.&quot; Ebbie stood up from her little rocking chair and headed to the front of the tent.&quot;You see over there?&quot; As her little hand points to another shop.<br>
<br>
Phallen looked at her with puzzlement,&quot;Yes, that little shop with bread for sale?&quot; he said taking another glance at the bakery.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yep.. that be it, just go there and ask for guidance.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Now what kinda of baker weilds powers of the intellect?&quot; He asked himself.<br>
<br>
&quot;Go on lad.. don't be afraid, It's not like she weilds powers from the dragons ya know!&quot;  She laughed.<br>
<br>
Phallen looked at Ebbie with a horrified look, &quot;What do you mean?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I am only teasing you.. sheesh.. loosen up..&quot;<br>
<br>
Ebbie walked back to her chair shaking her head in disbelief, &quot;You know, for a second I coulda sworn you believed me&quot; she snickered with amusement.<br>
<br>
&quot;Heh..&quot; Phallen turned his back to her and rolled his yes. &quot;That shit ain't funny&quot; he thought to himself as he walked over to the bakery.<br>
<br>
Temeilion was still screaming to the top of his lungs about his dragon gear and how good his deals were, and people were all taken up in awe at the nice artifacts he had layed out on his vendor table.<br>
<br>
Walking towards the bakery Phallen could smell the sweet aroma of freshly baked bread, &quot;This smells rather good!&quot; he thought to himself. As he got closer to the bakery, merchants tried desperately to lure him with great deals.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sir, Sir! You won't believe what I got here today! Check it out! Hottest deals on Crystal chittin gear! Here, for prime example, Crystal Spied eyes!!! only 400 Platinum pieces!!&quot; Shouted one dwarf merchant.<br>
<br>
